reviews.text:
What we ordered was the Thick Potato Noodle (1) and Ramen (3).
The options that are defined with "stir" are served without the soup, take note. 
We added meatballs and lobster balls on our order. 
Overall the soup was okay. The servings were huge. The thick potato noodle was a first for me, the texture is similar to eating a bubble gum. Its chewy. Very heavy in the stomach.
reasonably priced food but very crowded and uncomfortable seats
The sauce is very delicious and the flat rice noodle is very springy!

Good food and accommodating of my vegan diet. Need to communicate in cantonese, however, so be sure to know what you're ordering. As with other places, straws are unnecessarily handed out for all cans and bottles.
Very good taste and noodle here is very good. Not expensive at all

result.adr_address: 香港元洲北河街165-167號
result.name: 川味美食 (福榮街分店)

reviews.text: 撈薯粉👍

種類款式多樣化，價錢又大眾化，即合理，而食物味道亦太美味了，用價廉物美來形容，真是最好不過。裡面的店員雖然說話粗聲粗氣，又大聲，但總是好有禮貌對待每一客人。就算只欠五分鐘左右才到下午茶時段，佢哋都唔會與客人斤斤計較，會只當下午茶收費及服務。試過其他分店（係呢間的分店）的服務後，發現這間雖然環境超細小，但服務質素比其他分店好好多，簡直天差地別，令我想再下次光臨。亦可能因為食物美味而服務質素太好的緣故，這間總是人山人口，多人光顧。
態度極差，落9錯單，食物難食
麵湯尚可，但比一般店舖少下味精，餸菜一般，收費中等。
拉麵，米線，薯粉，有湯底及捞麵選擇，另外可以再加餸，我就喜歡3號拉麵非常好吃
